                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49030",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Based on your [the reporter] (private) feedback, that I requested, I agree that this is only a workaround. However, if you are looking to post files with Zend_Rest_Client you are doing it wrong. Zend_Rest_Client is a high level client, that is intended for use with Zend_Rest_Server, as it is designed at present. Future implementations will likely be able to talk to different types of servers, but as it is now, Zend_Rest_Client is only a convenient way to call class methods on the server as rest methods. Therefore, if you want to post a file, you should create a method on the server that can take a filename and file contents as arguments. An example server would look like this:\r\n{code}\r\n<?php\r\nclass TestClass {\r\n    public function saveFile($contents, $filename)\r\n    {\r\n        $path = '\/tmp\/' . $filename;\r\n        file_put_contents ($path, $contents);\r\n        return file_get_contents($path);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass RestController extends Zend_Controller_Action\r\n{\r\n    public function indexAction()\r\n    {\r\n        $server = new Zend_Rest_Server();\r\n        $server->setClass('TestClass');\r\n        $server->handle($_REQUEST);\r\n        exit();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nA request to this method could look like this:\r\nhttp:\/\/localhost\/rest\/?method=saveFile&contents=bogus&filename=harry_potter\r\n\r\nAnd the response would be:\r\n{code}\r\n<TestClass generator=\"zend\" version=\"1.0\">\r\n  <saveFile>\r\n    <response>bogus<\/response>\r\n    <status>success<\/status>\r\n  <\/saveFile>\r\n<\/TestClass>\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-08T22:46:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-08T22:46:37.000+0000"
                },
